text: SunriseA Song of Two Humans
title: Sunrise

text: This song of the Man and his Wifeis of no place and every place:
title: Sunrise

text: you might hear it anywhere at any time.
title: Sunrise

text: For wherever the sun risesand sets in the city's turmoil or
title: Sunrise

text: under the open sky on the farm
title: Sunrise

text: life is much the same:sometimes bitter, sometimes sweet
title: Sunrise

text: Summertime... vacation time
title: Sunrise

text: Among the vacationists wasa Woman of the City.
title: Sunrise

text: Several weeks had passed since her comingand still she lingered.
title: Sunrise

text: "They used to be like children, carefree...always happy and laughing..."
title: Sunrise

text: "They used to be like children, carefree...always happy and laughing..."
title: Sunrise

text: "Now he ruins himself for that woman from the city -Money-lenders strip the farm - "
title: Sunrise

text: "Now he ruins himself for that woman from the city -Money-lenders strip the farm -
title: Sunrise

text: and his wife sits alone."
title: Sunrise

text: "Tell me!You are all mine?"
title: Sunrise

text: "Sell your farm...come with me to the City."
title: Sunrise

text: "...and my wife?"
title: Sunrise

text: "Couldn't she get drowned?
title: Sunrise

text: "...then overturn the boat...it will look like an accident."
title: Sunrise

text: "Leave this behind...come to the City!"
title: Sunrise

text: "Come to the City!"
title: Sunrise

text: "...after the boat has capsized,save yourself with these bulrushes."
title: Sunrise

text: "The rushes will hold you up.
title: Sunrise

text: Scatter them before you reach the shoreand tell everyone she drowned by accident."
title: Sunrise

text: "We're going for a trip across the water.I may not be back for quite a while."
title: Sunrise

text: "Don't be afraid of me!"
title: Sunrise

text: "Don't be afraid of me!"
title: Sunrise

text: "God is giving you,in the holy blonds of matrimony, a trust.
title: Sunrise

text: She is young... and inexperienced.Guide her and love her..."
title: Sunrise

text: "...keep and protect her from all harm."
title: Sunrise

text: "Wilt thou LOVE her?"
title: Sunrise

text: "Forgive me!"
title: Sunrise

text: "Manicure?"
title: Sunrise

text: "You'd look grandwith a high polish!"
title: Sunrise

text: "Come again!"
title: Sunrise

text: "Thank you!And you must come and see us some time."
title: Sunrise

text: "Congratulations! She is thesweetest bride I've seen this year."
title: Sunrise

text: "FARMERS!
title: Sunrise

text: If you want to sell your homeand move to the city... We Pay Cash!"
title: Sunrise

text: "Hit the hole...make the little piggy roll!"
title: Sunrise

text: MIDSUMMER(Peasant Dance)
title: Sunrise

text: "We'll sail home by moonlight...another honeymoon."
title: Sunrise

text: "...I couldn't give up hope.I know the tides... I went around the Point..."
